{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p>I recently came across this beautiful, evocative quote from Virginia Woolf's <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Waves\"><em>The Waves</em></a>:\n <br>\n<br>\n  </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\"There was a star riding through clouds one night, &#x26; I said to the star, 'Consume me'.\"  </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> <br>\nI think the feeling of this is perfectly captured in John Adams' <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/music/tomserviceblog/2014/mar/11/symphony-guide-john-adams-harmonielehre-tom-service\"><em>Harmonielehre</em></a>, particularly the last movement:</p>\n<div style=\"position:relative;padding-bottom:48%;padding-top:30px;height:0;overflow:hidden;\">\n  <iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/3X-IUE_muQA\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div>\n<p>You can read more about <em>Harmonielehre</em> in John Adams' own <a href=\"https://www.earbox.com/harmonielehre/\">piece description</a>.</p>\n<p> <br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n  </p>","frontmatter":{"title":"John Adams and Virginia Woolf","image":"work/mwb-logo-text.jpg","description":"","date":"2019-02-27"}},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/synesthesia/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Synesthesia!"}},"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.1325028312570782,"src":"/static/618445d82c870810a6cdd3042c9468b5/8484e/mwb-logo-text.jpg","srcSet":"/static/618445d82c870810a6cdd3042c9468b5/6ad16/mwb-logo-text.jpg 200w,\n/static/618445d82c870810a6cdd3042c9468b5/8f1ca/mwb-logo-text.jpg 400w,\n/static/618445d82c870810a6cdd3042c9468b5/8484e/mwb-logo-text.jpg 800w,\n/static/618445d82c870810a6cdd3042c9468b5/2e8b4/mwb-logo-text.jpg 1000w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"pageContext":{"post_slug":"/blog/music-without-borders/","img_path":"work/mwb-logo-text.jpg","prev_slug":null,"next_slug":"/blog/synesthesia/"}}